// Virtual main: exit code = raw_len() + raw_quote_len() + multiline_len() + multiline_escape_len()
// == 4 + 3 + 3 + 4 == 14. Reaching it forces every raw / multi-line string literal through the
// lexer, parser, checker, VM and codegen as a plain `str`. A clean exit 14 on BOTH the VM
// (`teko run`) and the compiled binary (`teko build`) proves the feature holds end-to-end.
use m

(m::raw_len() + m::raw_quote_len() + m::multiline_len() + m::multiline_escape_len()) to i32
